briefTitle: Open-label Study to Evaluate the Efficacy and Safety of an Extended-cycle, Low Dose Combination Oral Contraceptive
officialTitle: A Multicenter, Open-label Study to Evaluate the Efficacy and Safety of an Extended-cycle, Low Dose, Combination Oral Contraceptive, Which Utilizes Ethinyl Estradiol During the Seven Day Interval Between Each 84-day Cycle
summary: This is an open-label, single treatment study. All subjects will receive one year of oral contraceptive therapy with DR-1011. Study participants will receive physical and gynecological exams, including Pap smear. During the study, all participants will be required to complete a diary.

primaryOutcome.measure: Annualized Pregnancy Rate (Pearl Index) For 91-Day Cycles by Cohort Using up to 14 Days Post-Last Combination Dose When Defining "On Drug" Pregnancy
